Privacy Policy for Job Application Tracker Extension
Effective Date: Nov 28th, 2024

Introduction
This Privacy Policy explains how the Job Application Tracker Chrome extension ("we", "our", "us") collects, uses, and stores your data. By using this extension, you agree to the practices outlined in this policy.

Data Collection
The Job Application Tracker extension collects data that you manually enter into the extension’s form (e.g., job title, company name, job ID, status, location, job link, and resume). All data entered is stored locally on your device using your browser's localStorage and is never shared with third parties or sent to external servers.

How We Use Your Data
The data you enter into the extension is used solely for the purpose of tracking your job applications. The data helps you manage and view details of the applications you've submitted. It is stored locally in your browser and can be accessed only by you.

Data Storage
All data is stored locally on your device and is not shared, transmitted, or stored on external servers. The data persists until you choose to delete it or uninstall the extension.

Security
We do not store any personal or sensitive information online. Your data is only stored in your browser’s local storage, which can only be accessed by you.

Third-Party Services
This extension does not use third-party services for data collection or analytics.

Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page, and the effective date will be updated. We encourage you to review this policy periodically to stay informed about how we protect your data.

Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or your data, please contact us at pachpanden2@gmail.com